Paul Klee called drawing, &lsquo;Taking a line for a walk&rsquo; and ever since I first saw his drawings I&rsquo;ve been really taken with the quality of his line.
Paul Klee, &lsquo;They&rsquo;re Biting&rsquo;
I just assumed he&rsquo;d drawn in ink on &ndash; possibly&ndash; damp paper, which I thought would explain the bleeding of the line and it&rsquo;s smudginess. I tried to mimic it again and again, with scratchy-nibbed dip-pens, different weights and finishes of paper; and I never got there.
